<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00548</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT IMPOSING THE COMPLETION OF THE REQUIREMENTS OF THE CONTINUING PROFESSIONAL EDUCATION (CPE) PROGRAMS ADOPTED BY PROFESSIONAL REGULATORY BOARDS AS A MANDATORY REQUIREMENT FOR THE RENEWAL OF PROFESSIONAL LICENSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Restores the Continuing Professional Education (CPE) requirement as a condition for the renewal of professional licenses. Repeals Section 20 of R.A. No. 8981, the PRC Modernization Act of 2000.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ESCUDERO, EVELINA G.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Reform</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Batocabe (060 2017-01-23)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON CIVIL SERVICE AND PROFESSIONAL REGULATION ON 2016-07-27</td></tr></table>